FBIS3-491 "drafr045_b_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia Pakistani Troops Accused of Rights Violations EA0703202394 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 7 Mar 94 EA0703202394 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the Great Somali People Language: Somali Article Type:BFN [Text] A spokesman for the Somali National Alliance [SNA] has said that Pakistani troops threw out wounded Somalis who had been admitted to their hospitals. The SNA spokesman described the move as the worst violation of human rights, adding that the Pakistani troops had previously committed such a violation. The spokesman added that some of the patients who had been ejected had died. He appealed to Somalis to take patients to Somali hospitals.
